Reporter:
<i> Country star juliette barnes</i>
<i> is in the news again.</i>
If she didn't leave her number,

11:19.885 --> 11:21.451
She doesn't want
to see you.

11:21.453 --> 11:22.885
<i>Cellphone footage is pouring in</i>
<i> from atlanta...</i>
Avery.

11:22.887 --> 11:24.319
<i> ...Where she allegedly</i>
<i> attacked a fan</i>

11:24.321 --> 11:25.987
<i> Who approached her</i>
<i> for an autograph.</i>

11:25.989 --> 11:28.689
<i> [ screaming ]</i>
<i>it's unclear as to why the star</i>
<i> attacked the fan.</i>

11:28.691 --> 11:31.358
<i> Perhaps it's the pressure</i>
<i> of her demanding schedule.</i>

11:31.360 --> 11:33.293
[ remote clicks ]
[ avery sighs ]

11:33.295 --> 11:35.695
There's something
really wrong.

11:35.697 --> 11:37.496
I should call her,
make sure she's okay.

11:37.498 --> 11:39.064
No, don't call her.

11:39.066 --> 11:41.699
If you do, you're just gonna get
sucked back into her craziness.

11:41.701 --> 11:44.435
He's right, man.
Juliette is officially
no longer your problem.

11:47.473 --> 11:49.306
[ crying ]
he doesn't want me anymore.

11:49.308 --> 11:51.141
You are not to leave this room
for the rest of the day.

11:51.143 --> 11:52.142
Why wouldn't he list--

11:52.144 --> 11:53.309
Now, sit.

11:53.311 --> 11:54.476
[ breathing heavily ]

11:54.478 --> 11:56.878
[ slurring ] wait. Wait.
Where are you going?

11:56.880 --> 12:00.214
Oh. [ chuckles ]
you're going to layla?

12:00.216 --> 12:01.815
I need you
more than she does.

12:01.817 --> 12:03.883
What you need
is to get sober.

12:03.885 --> 12:05.417
You know that you would
drop her in a second

12:05.419 --> 12:07.419
If I gave you
another shot at me.
[ laughing ] yeah?

12:07.421 --> 12:09.187
All you were to me

12:09.189 --> 12:10.588
Was a one-time bang
in a broom closet, sweetheart.
[ scoffs ]

12:10.590 --> 12:12.189
Shut up.
Hey --

12:12.191 --> 12:13.757
What the hell?
Hey!

12:13.759 --> 12:14.924
Sit!

12:14.926 --> 12:16.158
What is wrong with you?!

12:16.160 --> 12:19.394
You know you want me.
Everybody wants me.

12:19.396 --> 12:20.962
I couldn't
want a woman less.

12:21.998 --> 12:24.431
No wonder avery left you.

12:24.433 --> 12:25.598
What a waste.

12:27.535 --> 12:30.369
[ door opens, closes ]

12:30.371 --> 12:32.871
[ sighs ]

12:32.873 --> 12:33.872
That's all the books
packed up.

12:33.874 --> 12:35.406
Thank you.

12:35.408 --> 12:37.007
The rest of this stuff
should only take about an hour,

12:37.009 --> 12:37.974
And then
we can hit the road.

12:40.545 --> 12:42.111
I was thinking...

12:42.113 --> 12:44.046
Maybe we could
go to that gathering

12:44.048 --> 12:45.380
They're having
for your mother.

12:45.382 --> 12:48.015
Well, we really got to go
while there's still daylight.

12:48.017 --> 12:50.050
Don't you want to see
all the people, see the place?

12:50.052 --> 12:51.451
I<i> have.</i>

12:51.453 --> 12:53.386
It's just a...Sad lounge

12:53.388 --> 12:55.154
Where none of mama's dreams
came true.

12:57.024 --> 12:58.423
I still want to go.

12:58.425 --> 13:01.159
Fine.
I-I'm gonna stay here.

13:07.767 --> 13:09.433
[ guitar playing ]

13:09.435 --> 13:10.867
Yes.
I love that.

13:10.869 --> 13:12.301
Perfect.
Okay, all right.

13:12.303 --> 13:14.202
Want to give it a shot?

13:14.204 --> 13:15.136
Yeah.

13:15.138 --> 13:16.370
See what happens.

13:16.372 --> 13:18.405
[ cellphone bloops ]

13:18.407 --> 13:19.939
Man: 3...4...

13:19.941 --> 13:23.375
[ "in the name of your love"
playing ]

13:32.418 --> 13:34.651
Uh, kill it.
Just -- stop.

13:34.653 --> 13:35.985
[ music stops ]

13:35.987 --> 13:36.986
What's up?

13:36.988 --> 13:39.722
I'm just not feeling it.

13:39.724 --> 13:41.490
Okay, well, um...

13:41.492 --> 13:43.225
Should we sing one through
and just see what happens?

13:43.227 --> 13:44.726
No, I don't really see
what the point is

13:44.728 --> 13:46.461
If I know I don't like it,
you know?

13:46.463 --> 13:48.095
Well, it's definitely different
from what you're used to.

13:48.097 --> 13:49.262
Yeah.
I get that.

13:49.264 --> 13:51.397
But you don't need
to be afraid of that.

13:51.399 --> 13:52.464
[ chuckling ] oh.

13:52.466 --> 13:53.798
I'm not afraid.

13:53.800 --> 13:55.499
[ chuckles ]
I -- okay,
I don't mean "afraid."

13:55.501 --> 13:57.167
Just -- you don't
have to resist it

13:57.169 --> 13:58.935
Just 'cause it's new,
you know?

13:58.937 --> 14:00.937
I mean, let's try
a bunch of different stuff.

14:00.939 --> 14:02.738
Fine, but this isn't
a collaboration right now.

14:02.740 --> 14:03.839
This is a dictation.

14:03.841 --> 14:05.574
No, it's not.
Yeah, it is.

14:05.576 --> 14:07.475
You put this whole arrangement
together without even asking me.

14:07.477 --> 14:08.609
That's not true.
Yes, it I--

14:08.611 --> 14:09.977
You know,
maybe you were right before.

14:09.979 --> 14:11.144
Maybe you shouldn't
produce me.

14:12.147 --> 14:13.312
Okay.

14:13.314 --> 14:14.446
But just so we're clear,

14:14.448 --> 14:16.147
I'm doing exactly
what you asked me to do.

14:16.149 --> 14:18.282
No, that's when I thought
you got me, rayna.

14:18.284 --> 14:19.483
You don't.

14:19.485 --> 14:20.484
You know what?

14:20.486 --> 14:21.852
[ scoffs ]

14:21.854 --> 14:22.986
Maybe this whole thing
is a mistake.

14:28.192 --> 14:29.024
[ sighs ]
hi.

14:29.026 --> 14:30.859
[ laughs ]
finally.

14:30.861 --> 14:32.861
Hey. I know.
Listen, I can't stay, though.

14:32.863 --> 14:34.362
I got to take care
of this juliette situation.

14:34.364 --> 14:36.464
What? I thought
that's what you've been doing.

14:36.466 --> 14:39.099
I -- yes,
but there's more to it.

14:39.101 --> 14:41.000
Are these...Scratches?

14:41.002 --> 14:42.334
Stop it.

14:42.336 --> 14:44.169
Oh, my god.
It's nothing.

14:44.171 --> 14:45.537
What -- are you
sleeping with her again?!

14:45.539 --> 14:47.205
Hey, hey,
don't be ridiculous.
Why?!

14:47.207 --> 14:48.606
You've done it before!
She told me herself!

14:48.608 --> 14:49.873
Well, do you think
I give a damn about her?!

14:51.443 --> 14:52.608
Listen to me.

14:52.610 --> 14:55.010
Stop.
Listen to me.

14:55.012 --> 14:57.479
If I can just clean up this
juliette thing in the press --

14:57.481 --> 14:59.180
Ugh!
Okay, look,
I have a real shot

14:59.182 --> 15:01.182
At being the c.E.O.
Of luke's new company.

15:01.184 --> 15:02.516
What?
And if that happens,

15:02.518 --> 15:04.618
We'll never have to
deal with her again.

15:04.620 --> 15:07.721
Well -- so you won't be
my manager, either?

15:07.723 --> 15:09.956
No. I won't.

15:11.526 --> 15:14.994
Which will make things
a lot less complicated

15:14.996 --> 15:16.095
When you move in with me.

15:17.131 --> 15:19.131
What?

15:19.133 --> 15:20.132
Really?

15:20.134 --> 15:21.700
[ chuckling ] yeah.

15:25.705 --> 15:27.137
What are you still
doing here?

15:27.139 --> 15:28.972
Go.

15:30.475 --> 15:32.007
[ door opens ]

15:32.009 --> 15:33.408
Erin: Hello?

15:33.410 --> 15:35.676
Erin. Hey.
It's -- it's gunnar.

15:35.678 --> 15:37.644
How did you get
my number?

15:37.646 --> 15:39.412
Actually, it's, uh,
kind of a funny story.

15:39.414 --> 15:41.714
I called juliette's tour manager
and asked him for it,

15:41.716 --> 15:43.148
But he wouldn't
give it to me

15:43.150 --> 15:45.216
'cause of
some confidentiality policy.

15:45.218 --> 15:48.052
Anyway, so I told him I was
looking for a sound tech.

15:48.054 --> 15:50.487
[ chuckles ] you know,
'cause juliette had you fired.

15:50.489 --> 15:52.021
Quick thinking, right?

15:52.023 --> 15:53.989
Anyway, uh,
he finally gave it to me,

15:53.991 --> 15:55.523
And, uh,
now here we are.

15:55.525 --> 15:57.157
Okay.

15:57.159 --> 15:59.526
So...What do you want?

15:59.528 --> 16:01.861
Well, uh...

16:01.863 --> 16:03.395
You left your earring here,

16:03.397 --> 16:05.697
And I figured
you probably wanted it back.

16:05.699 --> 16:07.999
I wasn't wearing earrings
last night.

16:08.001 --> 16:09.166
Oh.

16:10.769 --> 16:12.034
Well, anyway, um,

16:12.036 --> 16:13.035
Since I got you,

16:13.037 --> 16:14.669
I was wondering
if, by chance,

16:14.671 --> 16:17.104
You wanted to catch my buddy
will lexington sing tonight.

16:17.106 --> 16:19.506
He's sort of giving
a surprise performance.

16:19.508 --> 16:21.941
Sure. Why not?

16:21.943 --> 16:24.910
Just text me the details,
and I'll meet you there.

16:24.912 --> 16:25.110
Bye, gunnar.

16:29.015 --> 16:33.717
¶ more than any other girl
I've ever known ¶

16:33.719 --> 16:34.918
[ indistinct conversations ]

16:34.920 --> 16:37.053
Man:
Well, what can I get you?

16:37.055 --> 16:38.354
Deacon: Club soda.

16:38.356 --> 16:40.356
Okay.

16:40.358 --> 16:42.391
¶ more than all things here
on earth I have been shown ¶

16:42.393 --> 16:43.625
Just passing through?

16:43.627 --> 16:46.527
Uh, I grew up here.

16:46.529 --> 16:48.896
Haven't been back
in 20 years, though.

16:48.898 --> 16:50.731
Still got family
in town?

16:50.733 --> 16:52.299
¶ as roses want the rain... ¶

16:52.301 --> 16:53.867
Not anymore.

16:55.470 --> 16:57.636
¶ I want you ¶

16:57.638 --> 17:00.038
¶ I want you ¶

17:00.040 --> 17:01.806
[ pinball clacks ]

17:01.808 --> 17:05.276
[ beeping, clicking ]

17:05.278 --> 17:07.777
Can we have a conversation about
what just happened, please?

17:09.914 --> 17:12.147
Look, I brought you
to nashville

17:12.149 --> 17:14.983
Because I could hear
the storyteller in your music,

17:14.985 --> 17:17.118
And that's what I'm trying
to get out there.

17:17.120 --> 17:19.053
I want to be able
to connect your voice

17:19.055 --> 17:21.121
To the audience,
like we talked about.

17:21.123 --> 17:23.323
You and I both know
the only reason you
brought me to nashville

17:23.325 --> 17:24.424
Is because
you need me --

17:24.426 --> 17:25.992
Because your label
was going under,

17:25.994 --> 17:26.926
You couldn't sign
a big nashville act.

17:26.928 --> 17:27.927
Yeah, I know.

17:27.929 --> 17:29.628
Okay, fine.
Sure, I needed you.

17:29.630 --> 17:31.096
But I would argue
you needed<i> me.</i>

17:31.098 --> 17:32.230
Oh, yeah?
And how do you figure that?

17:32.232 --> 17:33.831
The word is out on you.

17:33.833 --> 17:36.099
I mean, come on --
difficult, arrogant, abrasive.

17:36.101 --> 17:38.301
[ scoffs ] okay.
All of it kind of proving
to be true right now.

17:38.303 --> 17:40.236
Cool. Rayna, then let's just
cut ties. How 'bout that?

17:40.238 --> 17:41.103
No!

17:41.105 --> 17:42.137
Look, you're lashing out

17:42.139 --> 17:43.671
Because you're
questioning everything

17:43.673 --> 17:44.938
And you're doubting it.

17:44.940 --> 17:46.439
And I get it --
you're scared.

17:46.441 --> 17:49.241
But we have the opportunity
to do something special here.

17:49.243 --> 17:51.643
I wish you would trust me
on that.

17:51.645 --> 17:54.312
I just -- I'm -- I'm --

17:54.314 --> 17:57.748
I'm not -- I'm not hearing,
you know, what you're hearing.

17:58.917 --> 18:00.917
Did I ever tell you
about the first time
I heard your music?

18:01.819 --> 18:03.251
Come with me.

18:04.954 --> 18:07.421
Man:
...Getting some feedback.

18:07.423 --> 18:09.756
Rayna: Hey, girls.
Hey.

18:09.758 --> 18:11.624
Y'all know that boulevard song
you sang at the talent show?

18:11.626 --> 18:13.859
How'd you feel about singing
that for markus right now?

18:13.861 --> 18:15.493
Wait --
they're gonna sing my song?

18:15.495 --> 18:16.760
Yeah.

18:16.762 --> 18:18.194
I want you to hear
what I heard.

18:18.196 --> 18:20.296
Oh. So<i> now</i>
you want me to sing.

18:20.298 --> 18:22.031
Yeah. I do.

18:22.033 --> 18:23.599
Now? Right now?

18:23.601 --> 18:24.633
Yeah. Is that okay?

18:24.635 --> 18:26.368
Not really.

18:26.370 --> 18:27.635
Seriously?

18:27.637 --> 18:29.136
Hey, easy.

18:29.138 --> 18:30.937
What's the matter, honey?

18:32.507 --> 18:35.074
I just --
I don't want to.

18:36.777 --> 18:38.176
I'll be right back.

18:38.178 --> 18:39.577
Yeah.

19:39.438 --> 19:40.937
Hey.

19:40.939 --> 19:42.738
Mom, I don't want to sing,
okay?

19:42.740 --> 19:44.506
Okay. Okay.
You don't have to sing.

19:44.508 --> 19:47.241
I just want to make sure
you're all right.

19:49.011 --> 19:51.911
You usually jump
at the chance to sing a song.

19:51.913 --> 19:53.679
Seems like lately,

19:53.681 --> 19:56.248
You don't want anything
to do with music at all.

19:56.250 --> 19:58.550
What's the matter?

19:58.552 --> 20:01.452
After me and maddie sang
that song at the talent show,

20:01.454 --> 20:02.953
I was in the bathroom,

20:02.955 --> 20:05.388
And I overheard these girls
saying mean things.

20:05.390 --> 20:06.889
Like what?

20:06.891 --> 20:08.790
[ voice breaking ]
stuff about dad...

20:10.627 --> 20:13.628
...And how we should be
embarrassed to be onstage.

20:13.630 --> 20:16.764
Well,
that is...Ridiculous.

20:16.766 --> 20:19.733
You are<i> so</i> talented.

20:19.735 --> 20:22.936
You and your sister
should have nothing but pride

20:22.938 --> 20:24.704
In the gift that you have.

20:24.706 --> 20:27.807
No one's ever said
anything about me like that.

20:27.809 --> 20:29.275
You know, people...

20:29.277 --> 20:30.609
[ sighs ]

20:30.611 --> 20:32.277
...They're always
gonna be negative.

20:32.279 --> 20:35.380
But that can't ever take away
from what you do

20:35.382 --> 20:36.748
And how you feel
about it.

20:36.750 --> 20:38.983
I mean, you love music,
right?

20:38.985 --> 20:41.218
You love how you feel
when you're singing.

20:41.220 --> 20:42.285
Right?

20:42.287 --> 20:44.453
No one can ever
take that from you.

20:44.455 --> 20:46.488
[ audience cheering ]

20:46.490 --> 20:48.489
[ "run with me" plays ]

20:50.793 --> 20:54.795
¶ yeah, I am who I am
'cause I been where I been ¶

20:54.797 --> 20:58.565
¶ I've seen the wrong side
of the fence ¶

20:58.567 --> 21:02.902
¶ that's why I stay on the move
doin' what I do ¶

21:02.904 --> 21:06.505
¶ livin' it up while I can ¶

21:06.507 --> 21:08.807
¶ no, there ain't
no roadblocks, baby ¶

21:08.809 --> 21:10.742
¶ ain't no red lights, baby ¶

21:10.744 --> 21:12.510
¶ not a stop sign, baby ¶

21:12.512 --> 21:13.611
Get up there!
Go on!

21:13.613 --> 21:15.579
¶ on this rock 'n' roll road ¶

21:15.581 --> 21:20.149
¶ that gets wild ¶

21:20.151 --> 21:21.984
¶ wild and free ¶

21:21.986 --> 21:27.355
¶ better learn how to fly ¶

21:27.357 --> 21:30.891
¶ if you wanna run with me ¶

21:33.362 --> 21:34.694
Reporter:
<i> ...News from atlanta.</i>

21:34.696 --> 21:36.629
<i> The fan attacked</i>
<i>by juliette barnes this morning</i>

21:36.631 --> 21:39.098
<i> Has issued a formal apology.</i>

21:39.100 --> 21:41.366
<i> What happened this morning</i>
<i> with ms. Barnes</i>

21:41.368 --> 21:42.700
<i> Was my fault.</i>

21:42.702 --> 21:44.635
<i> I have been stalking her</i>
<i> for weeks,</i>

21:44.637 --> 21:46.670
<i> Seeking her out</i>
<i> at hotels and venues,</i>

21:46.672 --> 21:49.172
<i> Invading her privacy.</i>

21:49.174 --> 21:51.707
<i> Today, I took my harassment</i>
<i> too far,</i>

21:51.709 --> 21:54.142
<i> Provoking her</i>
<i> verbally and physically.</i>

21:54.144 --> 21:57.111
<i>Juliette barnes is a role model</i>
<i> for young women everywhere,</i>

21:57.113 --> 21:59.213
<i> And I am sorry</i>
<i> for any negative attention</i>

21:59.215 --> 22:01.548
<i> I may have brought upon her</i>
<i> by my behavior.</i>

22:01.550 --> 22:03.416
[ cellphone buzzes ]

22:05.887 --> 22:07.219
What can I do for you,
avery?

22:07.221 --> 22:08.620
What's wrong
with juliette?

22:08.622 --> 22:09.988
Nothing. Why?

22:09.990 --> 22:12.023
She attacked a fan.

22:12.025 --> 22:13.958
Who provoked her.
Oh, give me a break.

22:13.960 --> 22:16.026
That apology had
your fingerprints all over it.

22:16.028 --> 22:18.228
Is she losing it?
She having a breakdown?

22:18.230 --> 22:20.463
You left her.
Why do you care?

22:20.465 --> 22:22.231
Because I do, okay?

22:22.233 --> 22:24.800
She's the mother of my child,
and she's sick.

22:24.802 --> 22:27.068
She needs more than a manager
paying people off.

22:27.070 --> 22:28.803
She needs help,
and if you don't get it for her,

22:28.805 --> 22:29.904
So help me god --
look, look, look, man, look.

22:29.906 --> 22:33.173
The last time I saw her,
she was in her room,

22:33.175 --> 22:35.041
And she was fine.

23:06.673 --> 23:10.340
¶ was midnight
on the stormy deep ¶

23:12.711 --> 23:15.111
Woman: Yes, you remember
beverly got so peeved at you

23:15.113 --> 23:16.545
'cause you were
making a noise.

23:16.547 --> 23:17.913
[ deacon laughs ]
she stopped the band

23:17.915 --> 23:19.447
And told you to pipe down.
That sounds like my sister.

23:19.449 --> 23:20.614
Oh. Excuse me one second.
Pardon me.

23:20.616 --> 23:21.681
Hey.

23:21.683 --> 23:22.848
Hey.
I'm so glad you came.

23:22.850 --> 23:24.182
Packed, ready to go.

23:24.184 --> 23:25.950
No. No, we can't go now.
Look at this place.

23:25.952 --> 23:27.551
All these people here,
they showed up for your mom.

23:27.553 --> 23:29.219
Who are they all?

23:29.221 --> 23:31.921
Well, they're friends
from around town.

23:31.923 --> 23:34.256
They're people who'd come here
and hear her sing.

23:34.258 --> 23:36.291
Let me introduce you now.
Come on.

23:36.293 --> 23:37.525
Please, I --
hey.

23:37.527 --> 23:39.260
This is scarlett.
This is beverly's daughter.

23:39.262 --> 23:41.128
This is my niece.
So nice to meet you,
honey.

23:41.130 --> 23:42.729
This is carol right here.
Nice to meet you, too.

23:42.731 --> 23:44.764
¶ when it's cold outside ¶
[ sighs ]

23:44.766 --> 23:46.699
¶ and the wind starts to blow ¶

23:46.701 --> 23:47.700
Excuse me.

23:47.702 --> 23:49.468
Hey.

23:49.470 --> 23:50.735
Hey.
Did you see will?

23:50.737 --> 23:52.870
He jumped offstage after his set
and disappeared.

23:52.872 --> 23:54.638
No, but have you seen erin?
Who?

23:54.640 --> 23:57.040
The girl who rode back
from atlanta with us last night.

23:57.042 --> 23:58.207
Why would she be here?

23:58.209 --> 24:00.342
[ chuckles ]

24:01.912 --> 24:03.378
Don't worry about it.

24:03.380 --> 24:04.645
[ indistinct conversations ]

24:04.647 --> 24:05.612
Hey.

24:05.614 --> 24:07.747
There you are!
Hey.

24:07.749 --> 24:09.749
I've been looking for you.
Same here.

24:09.751 --> 24:11.250
I wanted to say thank you
before I took off.

